    {
      "name": "epoch_in",
      "docs": [
        "Accept one chunk of an inbound epoch envelope from a batch operator.",
        "",
        "Solana's 1 232-byte transaction MTU forces production-scale OPP",
        "envelopes (multi-KB) to stream in pieces; the program assembles",
        "each operator's chunks in a per-(epoch, operator) staging PDA. A",
        "final zero-data call (`chunk_index == total_chunks`) finalizes the",
        "already-uploaded bytes. Once consensus is reached across the active",
        "group, the enclosed attestations are processed inline and the epoch",
        "cursor advances. A 1-chunk envelope is the degenerate data-upload",
        "case followed by the same terminal call."
      ],
      "discriminator": [
        85,
        70,
        55,
        132,
        50,
        198,
        135,
        115
      ],
      "accounts": [
        {
          "name": "operator",
          "writable": true,
          "signer": true
        },
        {
          "name": "config",
          "writable": true
        },
        {
          "name": "operator_registry",
          "writable": true
        },
        {
          "name": "epoch_deliveries",
          "docs": [
            "Per-epoch consensus tracker. Lazily inited on the first delivery",
            "(i.e. the first operator to land their terminal call for this epoch)."
          ],
          "writable": true
        },
        {
          "name": "chunk_buffer",
          "docs": [
            "Per-(epoch, operator) staging buffer. Same `init_if_needed` +",
            "`payer = operator` pattern the program already uses for",
            "`EpochDeliveries`. Closed by the handler when the operator's",
            "zero-data terminal call finalizes the envelope, returning the",
            "rent lamports — net cost to the operator across the full epoch is zero."
          ],
          "writable": true
        },
        {
          "name": "inbound_envelopes",
          "docs": [
            "Singleton inbound-envelope log. Append-and-prune on every",
            "consensus-reach (see `finalize_envelope`)."
          ],
          "writable": true
        },
